  "title": "Question on the page \"Common parameters\"",
  "body": "Hi! I have a documentation issue on InstantSearch.js. I could not find what I was looking for on the page \"[Common parameters](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets-common-api.html)\".\r\n\r\n<!-- Describe what you're looking for here. -->\r\n\r\nTrying desperately to get the Hits widget to work. It doesn't recognize any referential tags, meaning I can't display search results. Currently, they just come up empty. \r\n\r\nThis is my widget. As you can see, I got desperate but none of the bellow works.\r\n \r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n    container: \"#hits\",\r\n    templates: {\r\n      empty: \"No Results.\",\r\n      item:\r\n        \"{{html}} {{value}} {{title}}<em>Hit {{objectID}}</em>: {{_highlightResult.title.value}}\"\r\n    },\r\n    escapeHits: true,\r\n    transformItems: items => items.map(item => item)\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```",
